%% Classical GoF Builder (as described in Design Patterns, 1994)
classDiagram
    class Director {
        -builder: Builder
        +construct() Product
    }
    class Builder {
        <<abstract>>
        +build_part_a()*
        +build_part_b()*
        +get_result()* Product
    }
    class ConcreteBuilder {
        -product: Product
        +build_part_a()
        +build_part_b()
        +get_result() Product
    }
    class Product {
        -part_a
        -part_b
    }

    Director --> Builder : uses
    Builder <|-- ConcreteBuilder : implements
    ConcreteBuilder --> Product : builds

    note for Builder "In GoF the Builder is an abstract class\nwith mutable internal state and side-effectful\nbuild_part_* methods. Rust finds this awkward:\nshared mutable state across abstract methods\nfights the borrow checker."
